TOOL_USE: Write({"file_path": "/home/joe/Documents/repo/skill/sci-draw/.claude/_eval_sandbox_home/.claude/plans/fluttering-wiggling-origami.md", "content": "# Lab Sensor Dashboard — Implementation Plan\n\n## Context\n\nThe user needs an interactive web dashboard to visualize lab sensor data from PostgreSQL. Since no database schema or connection details are provided yet, the plan builds a fully functional demo using **SQLite + simulated data** that can be trivially swapped to PostgreSQL by changing the connection string. The architecture supports the two core requirements: **time-range filtering** and **device-type filtering**.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nsensor_dashboard/\n├── app.py              # Dash app entry point, layout, callbacks\n├── db.py               # Database layer (SQLite by default, PostgreSQL-ready)\n├── data_generator.py   # One-time script to seed simulated sensor data\n├── requirements.txt    # dash, plotly, pandas, sqlalchemy, psycopg2-binary\n└── assets/\n    └── style.css       # Minor layout tweaks\n```\n\n### Stack\n\n- **Dash** (Plotly's web framework) — interactive UI with Python-only callbacks, no JavaScript needed\n- **Plotly Express/Graph Objects** — charts rendered in the browser\n- **SQLAlchemy** — database abstraction; swap `sqlite://` to `postgresql://` in one line\n- **Pandas** — query results → DataFrames for Plotly\n\n### Database Schema (designed for a typical lab sensor setup)\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE sensor_readings (\n    id          INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n    timestamp   DATETIME NOT NULL,\n    device_id   TEXT NOT NULL,\n    device_type TEXT NOT NULL,   -- e.g., 'temperature', 'humidity', 'pressure', 'ph'\n    value       REAL NOT NULL,\n    unit        TEXT NOT NULL    -- e.g., '°C', '%', 'hPa', 'pH'\n);\n\nCREATE INDEX idx_readings_ts   ON sensor_readings(timestamp);\nCREATE INDEX idx_readings_type ON sensor_readings(device_type);\n```\n\nSimulated data: 7 days of readings from 5 device types × 3 devices each, every 60 seconds → ~50,400 rows. Realistic patterns with diurnal cycles and noise.\n\n### Dashboard Layout\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  🔬 Lab Sensor Monitor                       │\n├──────────────┬───────────────────────────────┤\n│  Filters     │                               │\n│              │  ┌─ Line Chart ─────────────┐ │\n│  Date Range  │  │  Time-series of selected │ │\n│  Picker      │  │  device(s)               │ │\n│              │  └──────────────────────────┘ │\n│  Device Type │                               │\n│  Dropdown    │  ┌─ Current Values ─────────┐ │\n│              │  │  Gauge/indicator cards    │ │\n│  Auto-refresh│  │  for each device          │ │\n│  Toggle      │  └──────────────────────────┘ │\n│              │                               │\n│              │  ┌─ Heatmap ────────────────┐ │\n│              │  │  Device × Hour avg.       │ │\n│              │  └──────────────────────────┘ │\n├──────────────┴───────────────────────────────┤\n│  Data Table (last N rows)                     │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Callbacks\n\n1. **Filter → Line Chart**: When date range or device type changes, query DB and update line chart\n2. **Filter → Gauge Cards**: Update current-value indicator cards\n3. **Filter → Heatmap**: Recompute device×hour matrix\n4. **Auto-refresh Interval**: Every 10 seconds, re-query for the latest readings within current filter window\n5. **Filter → Data Table**: Show most recent matching rows\n\n### PostgreSQL Migration\n\nSwap `db.py` line:\n```python\n# SQLite (demo)\nengine = create_engine(\"sqlite:///sensor_data.db\")\n\n# PostgreSQL (production)\nengine = create_engine(\"postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/dbname\")\n```\nUse `psycopg2-binary` as the PostgreSQL driver. Add `pool_pre_ping=True` and `pool_recycle=3600` for production.\n\n## Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `sensor_dashboard/requirements.txt` | Pinned dependencies |\n| `sensor_dashboard/data_generator.py` | Creates SQLite DB and seeds ~50k simulated readings |\n| `sensor_dashboard/db.py` | SQLAlchemy engine, query functions with time/type filtering |\n| `sensor_dashboard/app.py` | Dash app: layout + callbacks |\n| `sensor_dashboard/assets/style.css` | Basic styling |\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n1. **Write `requirements.txt`** — dash, plotly, pandas, sqlalchemy\n2. **Install dependencies** into `sensor_venv`\n3. **Write `data_generator.py`** — schema + seed script, run once\n4. **Write `db.py`** — engine creation + `get_readings(start, end, device_types)` and `get_current_values()`\n5. **Write `app.py`** — full Dash layout with DatePickerRange, Dropdown, Interval, 3 chart areas, data table, and callbacks\n6. **Write `assets/style.css`** — minor layout polish\n7. **Run and verify** — launch `python app.py`, open browser at `localhost:8050`, confirm all filters work\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Run `python data_generator.py` → confirms DB creation and row count\n2. Run `python app.py` → opens at http://127.0.0.1:8050\n3. Test interactions:\n   - Change date range → charts update\n   - Select/deselect device types → charts filter\n   - Toggle auto-refresh → charts poll for new data\n   - Verify heatmap shows sensible device×hour patterns\n"})
